│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `instcombine` pass incorrectly simplifies the instruction `%cmp = icmp samesign ult i8 │
│ %umax, -32` to `false`. The `samesign` predicate for an integer comparison is true if and  │
│ only if both operands have the same sign (both negative or both non-negative). If the      │
│ signs are the same, the result of `icmp samesign ult` is the same as `icmp ult`;           │
│ otherwise, the result is `false`.                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
